The Lebanese "Party of God" continued to scare Katiuscia rockets on the heights of the Golan until the early lights of dawn, when in Israel, at four in the morning, the invitation of the authorities to leave the shelters.&nbsp;
The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, today presided over a meeting in videoconference of the Heads of State and Government G7>, convened after the Iranian attack against Israel. At the end of the discussion - we read in the final communiqué - the G7 leaders adopted a joint declaration that firmly condemns the launch of drones and missiles from Iran, reaffirming full support for the security of Israel. The G7 stressed the need to avoid further escalation, inviting the parties to refrain from actions aimed at sharpening tension in the region. To this end, the G7 appealed to end the crisis in Gaza through the cessation of hostilities and the release of the hostages by Hamas. Finally, they ensured the continuation of humanitarian aid to the Palestinian population.
The Israeli prime minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, had ensured he was prepared to react and had a night telephone conversation with US President Joe Biden. Tel Aviv claims to have dropped 99% of drones and missiles, a success guaranteed by the support of U.S., Great Britain and Jordan.
